 \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2935, \"end\": 2948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deutsche_Bahn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deutsche Bahn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deutsche_Bahn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deutsche_Bahn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Traffic only returned to normal on Monday morning, but only after around 800,000 customers had faced disruption.\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3110, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more from Sky News:Venezuela's president wins third termCommunity devastated by rocket attack on football pitch  Opening ceremony held under heavy security  More than 300,000 spectators lined the banks of the River Seine for Friday evening's opening ceremony which included the athletes' parade through the heart of Paris on a flotilla of barges and riverboats.\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3127, \"end\": 3135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.758317896521099e-13, \"text\": \"Sky News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\"}, {\"begin\": 3136, \"end\": 3145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"score\": 0.5684993554718781, \"rank\": 0.7590169457686213, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\"}, {\"begin\": 3326, \"end\": 3337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 3433, \"end\": 3438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9915706233566044e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France deployed 45,000 police, 10,000 soldiers and 2,000 private security agents to secure the celebratory event.\", \"from\": 3480, \"to\": 3593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3480, \"end\": 3486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.1940851178844292e-12, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Snipers were on rooftops and drones kept watch from the air.\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But while the capital was locked down for the opening ceremony, security elsewhere in the country has been lighter.\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3772, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Be the first to getBreaking News  Install the Sky News app for free\", \"from\": 3774, \"to\": 3841, \"entities\": []}]}"